    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-23T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-23T22:00:00-05:00" n="669"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Brazil/5191: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-23T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 23, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3612. From Scheuer, OEW, for Winans. Your 4374, September 14. Pleased to learn
                    reaction Brazilian Government favorable. We accept the recommendation that you
                    negotiate separately for each commodity. Contracts must incorporate principles
                    and general points contained in A–2164, August 30. Contracts will have to be
                    submitted to Washington for approval before execution. [Scheuer.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
